HEADWORD: Busket
<hw>Bus"ket</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Bosket</er>, <er>Bouquet</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A small bush;
also, a sprig or bouquet.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Spenser.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A part of a garden devoted to shrubs.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Buskin</ent>⟦br⟧
